headline: Carnival Earnings Beat Is a Relief for Cruise Stocks
summary: Carnival  beat earnings expectations and issued strong 2026 guidance Friday.  The cruise operator reported adjusted earnings of 34 cents per share on sales of $6.3 billion—a fourth-quarter record—in the three months to November 30.  Carnival’s first quarter EPS guidance is a touch below Wall Street’s expectations, but its full-year outlook for $2.48 per share is higher than the $2.44 consensus.
